	<h2>Web Design and Development</h2>
	<hr />
	<h3>The Procedure</h3>
	<ol>
		<li>
			Have contact with us about a Website / Web Application Project could be via phone or email;
		</li>
		<li>
			The client will be interviewed by means a phone interview or a questionnaire can also be sent for the client's convenience;
		</li>
		<li>
			A document called a Software Specification Requirement (SRS) signed by our Web Developer will be sent to the client to be read and signed as an agreement to the specifications and requirements based on the interview whether personal or via a questionnaire;
		</li>
		<li>
			Once the client has agreed by means of signing the doc and emailing a scanned version to us, a mandatory 25% deposit is required before the project officially commences;
		</li>
		<li>
			The Planning and Prototyping phases of the project commence sequentially following the specs stipulated on the SRS (Signed) document;
		</li>
		<li>
			The proposed designs and/or prototype will be shown to the client for approval/ feedback, another 25% deposit is mandatory prior to the final build and testing of the product;
		</li>
		<li>
			Final changes will be made the product will undergo the stages of testing, debugging and documenting respectively, once quality testing is done the product will be hosted temporarily on a temporary domain for the client to examine before hosting it on a production server;
		</li>
		<li>
			Once the client is satisfied with the product, it'll remain with MSDC until the remaining amount is fully paid up, this is to ensure payment guarantee as we cannot control the site should the client have the site hosted by a third party;
		</li>
		<li>
			The client can opt to have MSDC Inc (Pty) Ltd set up hosting on their behalf at a fee that depends on the client's requirements. However, the client is free to have the site hosted by a hosting provider of their choice. However, a change of ownership fee of R1000.00 in order for the client to take ownership if the source code applies should the client wish to do such. Clients are advised to opt for a Windows hosting environment as MSDC Inc (Pty) Ltd specializes in ASP.Net as opposed to PHP or any other framework.
